javax.json

Interface JsonNumber

  • All Superinterfaces:
    JsonValue

    public interface JsonNumber
extends JsonValue
    JsonNumber represents an immutable JSON number value

    A BigDecimal may be used to store the numeric value internally. The BigDecimal may be constructed using int, long, BigInteger, double and String. Some of the method semantics in this class are defined using the BigDecimal semantics.

    Author:
    Jitendra Kotamraju

    • Method Detail

      • getNumberType

        JsonNumber.NumberType getNumberType()
        Returns a JSON number type for this number. A BigDecimal may be used to store the numeric value internally and the semantics of this method is defined using BigDecimal.scale(). If the scale of a value is zero, then its number type is INTEGER else DECIMAL.

        The number type can be used to invoke appropriate accessor methods to get numeric value for the number.

        For example: 

         
 switch(getNumberType()) {
     case INTEGER :
         long l = getLongValue(); break;
     case DECIMAL :
         BigDecimal bd = getBigDecimalValue(); break;
 }
        Returns:
        a number type
